    {
      "name": "Charts of the Fair Wind",
      "type": "equipment",
      "effects": [],
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "gm": "",
          "value": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Usage </strong>studied during daily preparations</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Requirements </strong>The charts’ benefits only apply within the geographic region of the Shackles.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">These aged charts of thick, yellowed parchment display rough representations of the Shackles’ major islands and the sea lanes between them. The detailed markings on these charts grant a +1 item bonus on Sailing Lore checks to navigate within the Shackles.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In addition, a multitude of wrinkles, stains, and blemishes mar the charts’ surfaces. Anyone meticulously studying the charts notices that these markings shift over time. The creases, smudges, and blotches on the map represent real weather conditions (such as clouds, rain, and wind) in the region, allowing an informed observer to determine the current weather patterns over the islands of the Shackles. The charts grant a +2 item bonus on Nature checks made to predict future weather conditions.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Activate </strong><span class=\"pf2-icon\">T</span>; <strong>Frequency </strong>once per day; <strong>Requirements </strong>You invested the map and plot out a course for a water vehicle that you pilot; <strong>Effect </strong>The pilot must make a Sailing Lore check against the DC of sailing their vehicle. </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Critical Success</strong> As success, but the bonus is 15%.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Success </strong>The vehicle gains a +10% item bonus to its speed so long as it follows the plotted course and doesn’t deviate from it.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Failure </strong>No effect.</p>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-def41dee-7fff-ba9c-fc60-64afd9269ebd\"> Critical Failure</strong> The vehicle takes a -5% item penalty to its speed for 24 hours.</p>"
        },
